<h2>View work item details and navigate tabs</h2>

<p>Work item details pages provide comprehensive information about a work item, organised into multiple tabs for easy navigation.</p>

<h3>Accessing work item details</h3>
<p>You can access work item details by:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Clicking on a work item title from the work items list</li>
    <li>Using the work item code in the URL: <code>/Project/Details/{id}</code></li>
    <li>Searching for the work item and clicking through</li>
</ul>

<h3>Work item navigation menu</h3>
<p>The left sidebar provides quick navigation to different sections:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Overview:</strong> Summary information, key metrics, and recent activity</li>
    <li><strong>Milestones, updates and successes:</strong> Progress tracking (expandable sub-menu)</li>
    <li><strong>RAG Tracking:</strong> Status history and changes</li>
    <li><strong>Work phases:</strong> Discovery, Alpha, Beta phases with dates</li>
    <li><strong>Team:</strong> Team members and their roles</li>
    <li><strong>Contacts & Governance:</strong> SROs, service owners, directorates, budget owners</li>
    <li><strong>Strategic Alignment:</strong> Outcomes, needs, problem statements, missions</li>
    <li><strong>Products:</strong> Associated products and work items</li>
    <li><strong>Dependencies:</strong> Work item dependencies and relationships</li>
    <li><strong>RAID:</strong> Risks, Actions, Issues, and Decisions</li>
    <li><strong>KPIs:</strong> Key performance indicators</li>
    <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Work item configuration and metadata</li>
</ul>

<h3>Overview tab</h3>
<p>The overview provides:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Work item summary and key information</li>
    <li>RAG status and history</li>
    <li>Recent status updates</li>
    <li>Key metrics and statistics</li>
    <li>Quick links to important sections</li>
</ul>

<h3>Milestones, updates and successes</h3>
<p>This expandable section includes:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Overview:</strong> Summary dashboard with counts</li>
    <li><strong>Milestones:</strong> Detailed milestone tracking</li>
    <li><strong>Monthly Updates:</strong> Required monthly submissions</li>
    <li><strong>Weekly Successes:</strong> Success story tracking</li>
</ul>

<h3>RAG Tracking</h3>
<p>View the complete history of RAG status changes, including:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Status transitions over time</li>
    <li>Who made each change</li>
    <li>Reasons for status changes</li>
    <li>Trends and patterns</li>
</ul>

<h3>Team tab</h3>
<p>See all team members, their roles, and time allocations. Add or edit team members from this tab.</p>

<h3>Contacts & Governance</h3>
<p>View and manage:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Senior Responsible Officers (SROs)</li>
    <li>Service owners</li>
    <li>Directorates</li>
    <li>Budget owners</li>
    <li>PMO contacts</li>
    <li>Primary contacts</li>
</ul>

<h3>Strategic Alignment</h3>
<p>Track how the work item aligns with strategic objectives:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Outcomes and their achievement status</li>
    <li>User needs</li>
    <li>Problem statements</li>
    <li>Mission alignment</li>
</ul>

<h3>Products tab</h3>
<p>View associated products and work items, including:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Product details</li>
    <li>Work item status</li>
    <li>Links to product operational reporting</li>
</ul>

<h3>Dependencies</h3>
<p>See work item dependencies and relationships:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Work items this depends on</li>
    <li>Work items that depend on this</li>
    <li>Dependency types and descriptions</li>
</ul>

<h3>RAID</h3>
<p>Manage Risks, Actions, Issues, and Decisions:</p>
<ul>
    <li>View all RAID items</li>
    <li>Create new items</li>
    <li>Track status and ownership</li>
    <li>Link related items</li>
</ul>

<h3>Tips for navigation</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Use the left navigation menu for quick access to sections</li>
    <li>The active tab is highlighted in the navigation</li>
    <li>Badge counts show the number of items in each section</li>
    <li>Use browser back/forward buttons to navigate between tabs</li>
    <li>Bookmark specific tabs using the URL with <code>?tab=</code> parameter</li>
</ul>

